            <div type="bibliography">
                <head>Bibliography</head>
                <p>Recorded in 1819 by Fr. Pacifico da Monte Cassiano and passed to Pietro Negri, Sardinian consul in Tripoli, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="cigiii"/>, <citedRange>5130</citedRange></bibl>;
                    transcribed in letters by Smith to Newton, <bibl><ptr target="thorn2007"/>, 
                        <citedRange>p.125</citedRange></bibl>, and published <bibl><ptr target="smith-porcher1864"/>, <citedRange>75</citedRange></bibl>; 
                        republished from a photograph <bibl><author>Reynolds</author> in <ptr target="thorn1999"/>,
                            <citedRange>74-5</citedRange></bibl>, whence <bibl><ptr target="cdlBE"/> <citedRange>2000.742</citedRange></bibl>, 
                    <bibl><title>SEG</title> <citedRange>49.2362</citedRange>.</bibl>
                </p>
            </div>
            
